<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/164:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-01T19:00:00+08:00">August 1, 1929—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 1—10:58 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>660. Legation’s 654, July 30, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Following from Reuter, Nanking, July 31st: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“The first Sino-Russian preliminary conference met yesterday
                                        afternoon at Manchuli, the Harbin Consul General, Melnikov,
                                        representing Russia and Mr. Tsai Yun-sheng, Commissioner for
                                        Foreign Affairs in Harbin, representing China. It is
                                        understood that they discussed questions of time and place
                                        for a formal conference.”</p>
                                </quote></item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Legation has been able thus far to confirm only the fact that
                                Soviet Consul General requested Chinese Commissioner of Foreign
                                Affairs to meet with him at Manchuli, July 31st.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Captain Powell, Naval Attaché, has proceeded from Harbin to
                                Manchuli.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
